# EdgeIntelligence: A Decentralised Cognitive Mesh for Real-Time Multi-Node Person Tracking

**Case Study Report**
**Subject:** Distributed Systems & Edge Computing
**Date:** March 2026

---


## 1. Project Overview

**EdgeIntelligence** is a fully decentralised, peer-to-peer (P2P) distributed system that performs real-time person tracking across multiple edge camera nodes — with **no central server**. Each node independently runs a computer vision pipeline and shares extracted intelligence across the mesh network, collaborating to build a unified view of all tracked identities.

The system is inspired by real-world challenges in surveillance, retail analytics, and campus security where deploying a central server is either infeasible, expensive, or a single point of failure.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Every node in the mesh is both a producer and consumer of intelligence. There is no master node by design. Leadership is dynamically elected using a distributed consensus algorithm.

---

## 2. Problem Statement

Traditional multi-camera person tracking systems rely on a **centralised architecture**: all video feeds are routed to a single powerful server that performs detection, tracking, and re-identification. This model has critical weaknesses:

| Problem | Centralised System | EdgeIntelligence |
|---|---|---|
| **Single Point of Failure** | Entire system fails if server goes down | Nodes continue operating independently |
| **Network Bandwidth** | Full video streams sent to server | Only 512-float feature vectors exchanged |
| **Scalability** | Server becomes bottleneck | Each node adds compute capacity |
| **Latency** | High — must reach central server | Low — processing happens at the edge |
| **Re-ID on Handoff** | Requires shared DB with central server | Mesh nodes share memory collaboratively |

**Goal:** Build a system where multiple cameras can independently detect people, extract compact mathematical "fingerprints" of their appearance, and share those fingerprints over a P2P mesh — so that if one camera sees a person and another camera later sees the same person, they can **recognise and re-identify** them using only the shared fingerprint, without ever sharing raw video.

---

## 3. System Architecture

The system follows a layered architecture with clear separation of concerns:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   UI Layer (dashboard.py)                │
│     Nerve Center — Real-time logs, video feed, stats    │
└────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘
                         │ UI Callbacks
┌────────────────────────▼────────────────────────────────┐
│                 Orchestrator (main.py)                   │
│              CognitiveMeshNode — wires all layers        │
└───────┬──────────────────────────────────┬──────────────┘
        │                                  │
┌───────▼────────┐               ┌─────────▼──────────────┐
│  Core Layer    │               │    Network Layer        │
│                │               │                         │
│  ┌──────────┐  │               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │
│  │ MLEngine │  │               │  │    P2PNode        │  │
│  └──────────┘  │               │  │  ┌─────────────┐  │  │
│  ┌──────────┐  │               │  │  │ MsgQueue    │  │  │
│  │FeatureEx │  │◄──────────────│  │  └─────────────┘  │  │
│  └──────────┘  │  Broadcast /  │  │  ┌─────────────┐  │  │
│  ┌──────────┐  │  Receive      │  │  │ BullyElect  │  │  │
│  │ ReIDTrack│  │  Intelligence │  │  └─────────────┘  │  │
│  └──────────┘  │               │  │  ┌─────────────┐  │  │
│  ┌──────────┐  │               │  │  │ VectorCommit│  │  │
│  │ Fusion   │  │               │  │  └─────────────┘  │  │
│  └──────────┘  │               │  └───────────────────┘  │
│  ┌──────────┐  │               └─────────────────────────┘
│  │LRUMemory │  │
│  └──────────┘  │               ┌─────────────────────────┐
└────────────────┘               │    Data Layer           │
                                 │  StimulusLoader         │
                                 │  (video / webcam / dir) │
                                 └─────────────────────────┘
```

### Key Design Choices
- **No central broker** — Nodes discover peers manually or passively (via incoming messages).
- **Binary vector payloads** — Only compact 512-dimensional float arrays are transmitted, not raw images.
- **Event-driven UI** — The UI receives all updates via a thread-safe callback queue.
- **Store-and-Forward** — If a peer is temporarily offline, messages are held in a per-peer queue and delivered when the peer reconnects.

