## 6. End-to-End Data Flow

The following trace describes what happens from camera frame to mesh-wide intelligence:

```
1. StimulusLoader.get_next_frame()
       │
       ▼ Raw video frame (numpy array, BGR)
2. MLEngine.process_frame(frame)
       │
       ▼ List of bounding boxes [(x1,y1,x2,y2,conf), ...]
3. MLEngine.get_padded_crop(frame, bbox)
       │
       ▼ Cropped person image (numpy array)
4. FeatureExtractor.extract_features(crop)
       │
       ▼ 512-D L2-normalized float vector ("feature ghost")
5. ReIDTracker.match(vector, memory)
       │
       ├─── MATCH FOUND ───► Fuse with LRUMemory.get() using FeatureFusion.fuse()
       │                     Update LRUMemory.put() with fused vector
       │                     Log match to UI
       │
       └─── NO MATCH ──────► Assign new UUID as global_id
                             LRUMemory.put(new_id, vector)
                             Log "New Identity Captured" to UI
       │
       ▼ (Either path leads here)
6. P2PNode.broadcast_intelligence(global_id, fused_vector, timestamp)
       │   Lamport clock incremented
       │   Payload = {global_id, timestamp, lamport_ts, sender_host, sender_port, vector, SHA-256 hash}
       │
       ▼ Message enqueued in each peer's ThreadSafeQueue
7. _queue_flush_loop() (background thread, every 1 second)
       │   Connect to peer (if not connected)
       │   Flush all queued messages over TCP
       │
       ▼ Received by peer's P2PNode._handle_client()
8. VectorCommitment.verify_commitment() → reject if hash mismatch
       │
       ▼ Valid payload
9. Lamport clock updated: max(local, received) + 1
       CLOCK callback → UI clock display updated
       PULSE callback → CognitiveMeshNode merges or stores in its LRUMemory
       QUEUE_STATUS callback → UI queue panel updated
```

