## 7. Software Engineering Principles Applied

| Principle | Application in this Project |
|---|---|
| **Single Responsibility Principle** | Each class has one job: [MLEngine](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/core/ml_engine.py#5-45) detects, [FeatureExtractor](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/core/feature_extractor.py#8-60) embeds, [ReIDTracker](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/core/tracker.py#3-42) matches, [P2PNode](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/network/p2p_node.py#12-268) networks. None overlap. |
| **Open/Closed Principle** | [StimulusLoader](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/data/stimulus_loader.py#4-54) is open for extension (new source types) without modifying existing logic. |
| **Abstraction / Information Hiding** | [P2PNode](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/network/p2p_node.py#12-268) hides all TCP, framing, and queue details behind [broadcast_intelligence()](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/network/p2p_node.py#162-188) and [add_peer()](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/main.py#53-55). |
| **Separation of Concerns** | `core/`, [network/](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/main.py#56-93), [ui/](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/ui/dashboard.py#38-93), and `data/` are strictly separated. The UI doesn't know about sockets; the network layer doesn't know about YOLO. |
| **Event-Driven Architecture** | The [ui_callback](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/tests/test_p2p.py#8-10) pattern decouples the network and core layers from the UI. The UI is purely reactive. |
| **Thread Safety** | [LRUMemory](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/core/memory.py#4-50), [ThreadSafeQueue](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/network/message_queue.py#4-33), and [NerveCenterUI](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/ui/dashboard.py#8-163) all use locks and queues to prevent race conditions across concurrent threads. |
| **Fault Tolerance** | Store-and-forward queues survive peer disconnections. Bully election survives coordinator failure. |
| **Cryptographic Integrity** | SHA-256 commitments ensure data has not been tampered with in transit. |
| **DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)** | The [ui_callback](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/tests/test_p2p.py#8-10) is a single unified channel for all events from the network layer to the UI, rather than multiple disparate function calls. |

