## 8. Testing Strategy

### Unit Tests — [tests/test_p2p.py](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/tests/test_p2p.py)

| Test Case | What it Verifies |
|---|---|
| **Fusion Math Test** | `FeatureFusion.fuse()` produces an L2-normalized output. Verified that `‖fused‖ = 1.0` with `numpy.isclose`. |
| **Store-and-Forward Test** | Node A queues a message when Node B is offline (`qsize == 1`). After Node B starts, the queue flushes to 0. |

### Integration Tests — [tests/test_distributed.py](file:///c:/Users/kanha/Documents/GitHub/EdgeIntelligence/tests/test_distributed.py)

| Test Case | What it Verifies |
|---|---|
| **Lamport Clock Test** | Start two nodes, send one message from A→B. Verify clock event `1` (A's send) and clock event `2` (B's receive = max(0,1)+1) are both emitted. |
| **Bully Election — Initial** | Start 3 nodes (ports 7001, 7002, 7003). After election, all nodes must agree that port **7003** is the coordinator. |
| **Bully Election — Fault Tolerance** | Kill node 7003. Wait for re-election. All surviving nodes must agree that **7002** is the new coordinator. |

> [!TIP]
> Run the tests from the project root:
> ```powershell
> $env:PYTHONPATH="."
> python tests\test_p2p.py
> python tests\test_distributed.py
> ```

